{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["32-JON-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "JON"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Yunus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of Yunus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Yunus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Jon \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Yunus \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "JON 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JON 1:1"}, "Now the LORD\u2019s", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s\nProper Name."]}], "caller": "+"}, " word came to Yunus the son of Amittai, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JON 1:2"}, "\u201cArise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and preach against it, for their wickedness has come up before me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JON 1:3"}, "But Yunus rose up to flee to Tarshish from the presence of the LORD. He went down to Joppa, and found a ship going to\nTarshish; so he paid its fare, and went down into it, to go with them to Tarshish from the presence of the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JON 1:4"}, "But the LORD sent out a great wind on the sea, and there was a mighty storm on the sea, so that the ship was likely to\nbreak up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JON 1:5"}, "Then the mariners were afraid, and every man cried to his god. They threw the cargo that was in the ship into the sea to\nlighten the ship. But Yunus had gone down into the innermost parts of the ship, and he was laying down, and was fast asleep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JON 1:6"}, "So the ship master came to him, and said to him, \u201cWhat do you mean, sleeper? Arise, call on your\nAllah!", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, gods"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Maybe your Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:6\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, gods "]}], "caller": "+"}, " will notice us, so that we won\u2019t perish.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JON 1:7"}, "They all said to each other, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s cast lots, that we may know who is responsible for this evil that is on us.\u201d So\nthey cast lots, and the lot fell on Yunus. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JON 1:8"}, "Then they asked him, \u201cTell us, please, for whose cause this evil is on us. What is your occupation? Where do you come\nfrom? What is your country? Of what people are you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JON 1:9"}, "He said to them, \u201cI am a Hebrew, and I fear the LORD, Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d (Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of heaven, who has made the sea and the dry land.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JON 1:10"}, "Then the men were exceedingly afraid, and said to him, \u201cWhat have you done?\u201d For the men knew that he was fleeing from\nthe presence of the LORD, because he had told them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JON 1:11"}, "Then they said to him, \u201cWhat shall we do to you, that the sea may be calm to us?\u201d For the sea grew more and more stormy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JON 1:12"}, "He said to them, \u201cTake me up, and throw me into the sea. Then the sea will be calm for you; for I know that because of me\nthis great storm is on you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JON 1:13"}, "Nevertheless the men rowed hard to get them back to the land; but they could not, for the sea grew more and more stormy\nagainst them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JON 1:14"}, "Therefore they cried to the LORD, and said, \u201cWe beg you, LORD, we beg you, don\u2019t let us die for this man\u2019s life, and\ndon\u2019t lay on us innocent blood; for you, LORD, have done as it pleased you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JON 1:15"}, "So they took up Yunus, and threw him into the sea; and the sea ceased its raging.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JON 1:16"}, "Then the men feared the LORD exceedingly; and they offered a sacrifice to the LORD, and made vows.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JON 1:17"}, "The LORD prepared a great fish to swallow up Yunus, and Yunus was in the belly of the fish three days and three nights.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "JON 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JON 2:1"}, "Then Yunus prayed to the LORD, his Allah, out of the fish\u2019s belly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JON 2:2"}, "He said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI called because of my affliction to the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He answered me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Out of the belly of Sheol", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I cried. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You heard my voice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JON 2:3"}, "For you threw me into the depths, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in the heart of the seas. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The flood was all around me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["All your waves and your billows passed over me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JON 2:4"}, "I said, \u2018I have been banished from your sight; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yet I will look again towards your holy temple.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JON 2:5"}, "The waters surrounded me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even to the soul. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The deep was around me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The weeds were wrapped around my head. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JON 2:6"}, "I went down to the bottoms of the mountains. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The earth barred me in forever: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yet have you brought up my life from the pit, LORD my Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JON 2:7"}, "\u201cWhen my soul fainted within me, I remembered the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My prayer came in to you, into your holy temple. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JON 2:8"}, "Those who regard lying vanities forsake their own mercy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JON 2:9"}, "But I will sacrifice to you with the voice of thanksgiving.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will pay that which I have vowed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Salvation belongs to the LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JON 2:10"}, "Then The LORD spoke to the fish, and it vomited out Yunus on the dry land.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "JON 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JON 3:1"}, "The LORD\u2019s word came to Yunus the second time, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JON 3:2"}, "\u201cArise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and preach to it the message that I give you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JON 3:3"}, "So Yunus arose, and went to Nineveh, according to the LORD\u2019s word. Now Nineveh was an exceedingly great city, three days\u2019\njourney across. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JON 3:4"}, "Yunus began to enter into the city a day\u2019s journey, and he cried out, and said, \u201cIn forty days, Nineveh will be\noverthrown!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JON 3:5"}, "The people of Nineveh believed Allah; and they proclaimed a fast, and put on sackcloth, from their greatest even to their\nleast. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JON 3:6"}, "The news reached the king of Nineveh, and he arose from his throne, and took off his royal robe, covered himself with\nsackcloth, and sat in ashes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JON 3:7"}, "He made a proclamation and published through Nineveh by the decree of the king and his nobles, saying, \u201cLet neither man\nnor animal, herd nor flock, taste anything; let them not feed, nor drink water;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JON 3:8"}, "but let them be covered with sackcloth, both man and animal, and let them cry mightily to Allah. Yes, let them turn\neveryone from his evil way, and from the violence that is in his hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JON 3:9"}, "Who knows whether Allah will not turn and relent, and turn away from his fierce anger, so that we might not perish?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JON 3:10"}, "Allah saw their works, that they turned from their evil way. Allah relented of the disaster which he said he would do to\nthem, and he didn\u2019t do it. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "JON 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JON 4:1"}, "But it displeased Yunus exceedingly, and he was angry. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JON 4:2"}, "He prayed to the LORD, and said, \u201cPlease, LORD, wasn\u2019t this what I said when I was still in my own country? Therefore I\nhurried to flee to Tarshish, for I knew that you are a gracious Allah, and merciful, slow to anger, and abundant in loving\nkindness, and you relent of doing harm. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JON 4:3"}, "Therefore now, LORD, take, I beg you, my life from me; for it is better for me to die than to live.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JON 4:4"}, "The LORD said, \u201cIs it right for you to be angry?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JON 4:5"}, "Then Yunus went out of the city, and sat on the east side of the city, and there made himself a booth, and sat under it in\nthe shade, until he might see what would become of the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JON 4:6"}, "The Allah the LORD prepared a vine, and made it to come up over Yunus, that it might be a shade over his head, to deliver\nhim from his discomfort. So Yunus was exceedingly glad because of the vine.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JON 4:7"}, "But Allah prepared a worm at dawn the next day, and it chewed on the vine, so that it withered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JON 4:8"}, "When the sun arose, Allah prepared a sultry east wind; and the sun beat on Yunus\u2019 head, so that he fainted, and requested\nfor himself that he might die, and said, \u201cIt is better for me to die than to live.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JON 4:9"}, "Allah said to Yunus, \u201cIs it right for you to be angry about the vine?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI am right to be angry, even to death.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JON 4:10"}, "The LORD said, \u201cYou have been concerned for the vine, for which you have not laboured, neither made it grow; which came\nup in a night, and perished in a night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JON 4:11"}, "Shouldn\u2019t I be concerned for Nineveh, that great city, in which are more than one hundred and twenty thousand persons who\ncan\u2019t discern between their right hand and their left hand; and also much livestock?\u201d\n"]}]}